  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If your ticket is waitlisted and the train has already departed, you will not be able to board the train. Waitlisted tickets do not guarantee a seat, and once the train departs, there is no option to travel with that ticket.\n\nRegarding the refund, you typically can request a refund for a waitlisted ticket that is not confirmed. For most Indian Railways tickets, if the ticket remains waitlisted up until the train's departure, you may be eligible for a full refund. However, specific rules can vary, so it's best to check the latest policies on the Indian Railways website or consult with the customer service at the station or through their helpline for details about how to initiate the refund process and any applicable fees.",
